{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.41",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 41,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 41",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 41 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:1",
      "text": "Hast thou not seen him? and hast thou not wondered at the things said of him? - Dost thou not fear because preparation has been made by me? for who is there that resists me?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:2",
      "text": "Or who will resist me, and abide, since the whole world under heaven is mine?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:3",
      "text": "I will not be silent because of him: though because of his power one shall pity his antagonist.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:4",
      "text": "Who will open the face of his garment? and who can enter within the fold of his breastplate?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:5",
      "text": "Who will open the doors of his face? terror is round about his teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:6",
      "text": "His inwards are as brazen plates, and the texture of his skin as a smyrite stone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:7",
      "text": "One part cleaves fast to another, and the air cannot come between them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:8",
      "text": "They will remain united each to the other: they are closely joined, and cannot be separated.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:9",
      "text": "At his sneezing a light shines, and his eyes are as the appearance of the morning star.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:10",
      "text": "Out of his mouth proceed as it were burning lamps, and as it were hearths of fire are cast abroad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:11",
      "text": "Out of his nostrils proceeds smoke of a furnace burning with fire of coals.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:12",
      "text": "His breath is as live coals, and a flame goes out of his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:13",
      "text": "And power is lodged in his neck, before him destruction runs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:14",
      "text": "The flesh also of his body is joined together: if one pours violence upon him, he shall not be moved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:15",
      "text": "His heart is firm as a stone, and it stands like an unyielding anvil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:16",
      "text": "And when he turns, he is a terror to the four-footed wild beasts which leap upon the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:17",
      "text": "If spears should come against him, men will effect nothing, either with the spear or the breast-plate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:18",
      "text": "For he considers iron as chaff, and brass as rotten wood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:19",
      "text": "The bow of brass shall not would him, he deems a slinger as grass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:20",
      "text": "Mauls are counted as stubble; and he laughs to scorn the waving of the firebrand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:21",
      "text": "His lair is formed of sharp points; and all the gold of the sea under him is an immense quantity of clay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:22",
      "text": "He makes the deep boil like a brazen caldron; and he regards the sea as a pot of ointment,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:23",
      "text": "and the lowest part of the deep as a captive: he reckons the deep as his range.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:24",
      "text": "There is nothing upon the earth like to him, formed to be sported with by my angels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.41.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:25",
      "text": "He beholds every high thing: and he is king of all that are in the waters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
